# Build context is the REPO ROOT (see Dockerfile header). Keep the image build
# lean and reproducible by excluding local/test cruft. The Dockerfile only COPYs
# the server module + the five shared/framework-go* modules, so most of the repo
# is never sent — but these patterns also trim those copied trees.
**/.git
**/.DS_Store
**/*_test.go
**/testdata/
**/test-artifacts/
**/.temporal/
**/node_modules/
**/build/
**/dist/
**/*.md
